From: Jeff Nott [jeff@collectorsfigurines.com]
Subject: How do I restore email?

My hard drive crashed. Fortunately, I had everything backed-up on a
CD. I restored all my files without problems except for my email
folders which I can not now open.

I am using Outlook Express and the original folders were stored at
C:\Documents and Settings\Administrator\Local Settings\Application
Data\Identities\{4903A7CA-6040-49BE-93FE-2461E20F0389}\Microsoft\Out
look Express. (The usual place Microsoft hides the emails.) I backed
up the emails by right clicking and using 'Go To' to send the
folders to the back up CDRom. (The folders are on the CD.)

When I tried to restore the folders, I created a same name folder
for each in Outlook Express, deleted the new folders from the above
location and copied my back-up folders into that location to take
their place.

In theory, and according to the magazine in front of me, this should
work.... but it does not.

I also tried the Import function in the File menu, but this looks
for messages and address books - not folders full of messages.

Does anyone know a work around that will restore my emails?

All help will be much appreciated.

Thanks.

Jeff Nott
http://www.collectorsfigurines.com
Dog figurines that often zoom in value.
Everything from the beautiful to the hilarious.

